 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 03 Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook focuses on the feature engineering pipeline for the Sentinel Sepsis-Associated AKI (SA-AKI) Early Warning System.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Strategy\n",
    "- **Missingness Indicators**: Missing data in EHR is highly informative. We explicitly create missingness flags before imputation.\n",
    "- **Rolling Windows**: To capture trends in vital signs and lab results, we compute rolling aggregates (mean, max, min, std) over time windows (e.g., 6h, 12h, 24h).\n",
    "- **Creatinine Velocity**: The rate of change in serum creatinine is a critical physiological marker for acute kidney injury.\n",
    "- **Composite Features**: Combining related measurements (e.g., BUN-to-creatinine ratio, shock index)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Colab setup: Uncomment if running in Google Colab\n",
    "# !pip install -q pandas numpy\n",
    "# from google.colab import drive\n",
    "# drive.mount('/content/drive')\n",
    "# %cd /content/drive/MyDrive/sentinel-poc/project_sentinel"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "sys.path.append(os.path.abspath('..'))\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.features import build_features as features\n",
    "\n",
    "data_dir = Path('../data')\n",
    "interim_dir = data_dir / 'interim'\n",
    "processed_dir = data_dir / 'processed'\n",
    "processed_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True, parents=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Loading cohort defined data...\")\n",
    "cohort_df = pd.read_parquet(interim_dir / 'cohort_defined.parquet')\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(cohort_df)} records.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Loading baseline creatinine...\")\n",
    "baseline_cr = pd.read_parquet(interim_dir / 'baseline_creatinine.parquet')\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(baseline_cr)} records.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Adding missingness indicators...\")\n",
    "df_with_missingness = features.add_missingness_indicators(cohort_df)\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape after missingness indicators: {df_with_missingness.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Adding rolling features...\")\n",
    "df_rolling = features.add_rolling_features(df_with_missingness)\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape after rolling features: {df_rolling.shape}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Imputing missing values...\")\n",
    "df_imputed = features.impute_values(df_rolling)\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape after imputation: {df_imputed.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Creatinine Velocity\n",
    "\n",
    "Creatinine velocity is perhaps the most important feature for predicting SA-AKI. It captures the **rate of change** of serum creatinine over recent time windows (e.g., 24 hours, 48 hours).\n",
    "\n",
    "A rapid rise in creatinine is a stronger predictor of imminent kidney injury than the absolute level of creatinine alone, as it directly reflects acute loss of glomerular filtration."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Calculating creatinine velocity...\")\n",
    "df_cr_velocity = features.add_creatinine_velocity(df_imputed, baseline_cr)\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape after creatinine velocity: {df_cr_velocity.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Adding composite features...\")\n",
    "df_composites = features.add_composite_features(df_cr_velocity)\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape after composite features: {df_composites.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Running master feature engineering pipeline...\")\n",
    "final_features_df = features.engineer_features(cohort_df, baseline_cr)\n",
    "print(f\"Final dataset shape: {final_features_df.shape}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save final features\n",
    "features_path = processed_dir / 'engineered_features.parquet'\n",
    "final_features_df.to_parquet(features_path)\n",
    "print(f\"Features saved to: {features_path}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Creating feature manifest...\")\n",
    "manifest = features.create_feature_manifest(final_features_df)\n",
    "print(f\"Generated manifest with {len(manifest)} features.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import json\n",
    "with open(processed_dir / 'feature_manifest.json', 'w') as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(manifest, f, indent=4)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Performing temporal train/val/test split...\")\n",
    "train_df, val_df, test_df = features.temporal_split(final_features_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Train shape: {train_df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Val shape:   {val_df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Test shape:  {test_df.shape}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "train_df.to_parquet(processed_dir / 'train_features.parquet')\n",
    "val_df.to_parquet(processed_dir / 'val_features.parquet')\n",
    "test_df.to_parquet(processed_dir / 'test_features.parquet')\n",
    "print(\"Data splits saved successfully.\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
